summary: Ugh! They didn’t even interview Taron (or then I missed it, but I doubt that)! Dammit. And Olavi Uusivirta and Kiti Kokkonen...
body:
Ugh! They didn’t even interview Taron (or then I missed it, but I doubt that)! Dammit. And Olavi Uusivirta and Kiti Kokkonen didn’t seem to be there, too bad. Tarja Halonen was there, tho. :D

Have to say, Carl-Kristian Rundman could have also be Finnish version of Moominpappa. There’s something very Moominpappa in his voice (something in his voice reminds me of the late Matti Ruohola).

Can’t wait to see the first episode. It has the Groke in it! (Have to say, no one will ever be good as the Groke than the late Tapio Hämäläinen - even tho the Groke was girl.) I’m very excited!

Oh. And it really isn’t fair that it will air in UK earlier. It shoul air first in here ‘cause, y’know, the Moomins are Finnish. :D
